  <description><![CDATA[<p>Enjoying a ski in/ski out location in <a data-udi="umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8}" title="Val Thorens">Val Thorens</a>, this delightful hotel enjoys spectacular views of the resort and surrounding peaks and is just a short walk to the shops, bars and restaurants. The Chambérot family ensure superb standards of comfort, service and fine cuisine in a cosy, relaxed atmosphere. As one of the only family-run hotels in resort, they pride themselves on a warm welcome and traditional Alpine charm.</p>
<h2>Bar and restaurant</h2>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">After a day of exploring the <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys</a>, the Hotel Le Sherpas lounge and bar area is a great place to socialise and catch up with friends and family with a glass of wine. Adorned with wood panelling and cosy throws, it certainly is a lovely place to warm up. When the sun is out you can make the most of the winter sun and admire the views of the surrounding mountains.</span></p>
<p>Half board meals are served in the warm and welcoming restaurant - each day you can enjoy a hearty buffet breakfast serving season products but of course, classic continental options will also be available. When its time for dinner you can enjoy a five course evening meal including a dessert buffet and weekly Savoyard themed evenings.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa </h2>
<p>After a day of skiing or snowboarding, you’ll have everything you need to relax at the Hotel Le Sherpa. Reserved for residents only, you can soothe any aches and pains in the jacuzzi or relax in the steam room. There is a panoramic cosmic sauna on the terrace, as well as the traditional sauna inside. For the ultimate treat a range of body treatments and massages are available - be sure to book with the hotel reception.</p>]]></description>
