  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Small double economy rooms </strong>sleep two people and are around 15m² with a double bed</p>
<p><strong>Traditional rooms </strong>sleep two to three people and are around 20m² with twin beds or a double bed,  plus an additional single bed and a balcony with mountain views.</p>
<p><strong>Panorama rooms </strong>sleep two to three people and are around 20m² with twin beds or a double bed, plus an additional single bed and a balcony with panoramic mountain views.</p>
<p><strong>Junior suites </strong>sleep two to four people and are around 30m², with a twin or double bedroom and an additional sofa bed on mezzanine level, and a balcony with mountain views</p>
<p>Economy rooms, traditional rooms and panorama rooms are available for sole occupancy. Please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Daily house keeping is included</li>
<li>Satellite TV</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities (on request)</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Iron</li>
<li>Bathrobes</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bath with shower head attachment </li>
<li>WC</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
